name: SE2-01 — THE SHOREFALL LANDING
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Baie Lazare (Anse Gaulettes / Lazare Picault, Mahé). Where Picault first kissed shore, the moon drew a silver line.\nFollow it south, when the tide leaves a bowl of glass.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare
Baie Lazare (Anse Gaulettes / Lazare Picault, Mahé)

name: SE2-02 — TIDE-BASIN RUNES
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Ros Sodyer Rock Pool (Anse Takamaka, Mahé). When the ocean exhales, stone remembers.\nRead the runes in the pool; they point by night, not day.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare
Ros Sodyer Rock Pool (Anse Takamaka, Mahé)

name: SE2-03 — THE HOLLOW AT BOILEAU
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Anse Boileau, Mahé. In Boileau's hollow, a blade once bit the map.\nLift the stone; the hillside whispers where to climb.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-04 — MIST OF MORNE BLANC
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Morne Blanc (Sans Souci ridge, Mahé). Above the bay, the mist keeps counsel.\nCount the five lights that survive the cloud.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-05 — LANTERN ON COPOLIA
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Copolia Trail granite dome, Mahé. On Copolia's stone, light bends the reef.\nArc the rope where the shoreline turns.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-06 — BEHIND THE CASCADE
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Cascade Waterfall (east interior, Mahé). Step behind the veil; water hides what stone declares.\nCoins of light pay passage west.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-07 — SAUZIER'S WHISPER
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Sauzier Waterfall (Port Glaud / near Port Launay, Mahé). Where the westward fall sings, follow the echo.\nIts measure climbs the coast to a hidden path.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare
Sauzier Waterfall (Port Glaud / near Port Launay, Mahé)

name: SE2-08 — THE HIDDEN PATH OF MAJOR
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Anse Major Trail (Bel Ombre, Mahé). A path with teeth and sea below.\nCount the cuts; they bite the heading east.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-09 — VACHE SENTINEL
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Vache Island (Île aux Vaches Marines). A cow by name, a sentinel by duty.\nCount the seven lights that never drink.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-10 — TEETH OF GEORGETTE
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Anse Georgette (Praslin). Among the teeth, a corner of night.\nThe feather points where the reef denies depth.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-11 — NIGHT AT INTENDANCE
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Anse Intendance, Mahé. Where the sea writes in thunder, the sand keeps one coin.\nTurn its scar toward the gentler shore.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-12 — ROYALE LANTERN
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Anse Royale, Mahé. Royale rests with two small lights.\nLoop the rope and climb to council.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-13 — COUNCIL OF MISSION LODGE
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Mission Lodge (Sans Souci, Mahé). Stones that watched the island's heart\ncast shadows pointing to the high road.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-14 — MISÈRE LOOKOUT
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). La Misère Viewpoint, Mahé. From hardship's ridge, count two knots of wind.\nThe lights below betray the turn.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-15 — TERNAY'S QUIET
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Baie Ternay / Port Launay Marine Park. In a bay that refuses storm,\nthe coral fingers name a number.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare
Baie Ternay / Port Launay Marine Park

name: SE2-16 — MAJOR'S RETURN
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Anse Major headland (return), Mahé. Four lights on the cliff's brow\nsend you back along the wound.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-17 — GAULETTES MARK
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Anse Gaulettes (Baie Lazare district), Mahé. By the marked stone where roads lean to the sea,\nscratch the sign and follow the feather.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-18 — BAY OF COINS
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Baie Lazare beach (wide). The bay keeps what the sea returns.\nSpiral the rope to test your course.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-19 — REEF GATE (DENISON)
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Lady Denison-Pender Shoal (outer). Six lights at the gate pretend to open.\nTurn your bow—home holds the lock.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare

name: SE2-20 — THE FIRST SHORE'S KEY
description: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare (Lazare Picault). Baie Lazare (return), Mahé. The loop returns where it began.\nThe first shore keeps the last key.

attributes.value: Chapter II — The Landing at Baie Lazare
